cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.SI

Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of Gaussian Processes and Multiple Kernel Learning for classification of neuroimaging data, which involves machine learning techniques and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning solutions, which falls under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper discusses the interpretation of the results in terms of known anatomical correlates of the disease, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neuroscience (cs.NE). Finally, the paper deals with high-dimensional data, which could also fall under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
